article.description: Michael Carey had 10 points, a career-high 15 rebounds and four assists Thursday night to help Wagner beat Bryant 65-56.
article.headline: Carey leads Wagner to 65-56 win over Bryant
article.linkText: Carey leads Wagner to 65-56 win over Bryant
article.story: NEW YORK -- Michael Carey had 10 points, a career-high 15 rebounds and four assists Thursday night to help Wagner beat Bryant 65-56. Corey Henson scored 11 and Japhet Kadji added 10 points for Wagner (9-5, 2-1 Northeast Conference). The Seahawks scored the first eight points and led until a 7-0 run, punctuated by a dunk by Dan Garvin, put Bryant up 47-43 with 6:40 left. But Wagner responded by scoring 22 of the final 28 points, including 9 of 11 free throws, to seal it. The teams both failed to shoot even 35 percent from the field, but Wagner outrebounded Bryant 45-36, including 17-10 on the offensive glass and the Bulldogs made just 14 of 24 (58.3 percent) free throws. The Seahawks made 15 of 20 from the foul line. Gavin led Bryant (5-11, 2-1) with 14 points. Curtis Oakley -- the nephew of former NBA-star Charles Oakley -- scored 12.
